# ADR-006: Incremental Evolution Toward Semantic Routing

## Status

Accepted

## Context

Embedding-based routing is desirable but premature.

Introducing vector stores and semantic infrastructure now would add complexity without immediate benefit.

## Decision

Architecture should evolve in stages:

### Stage 1

Keyword overlap on capabilities.

```
Query
 ↓
Capability matching
 ↓
Agent
```

### Stage 2

LLM-assisted selection.

```
Query
 ↓
Agent descriptors
 ↓
LLM selector
 ↓
Agent
```

### Stage 3

Embedding similarity.

```
Query embedding
 ↓
Descriptor embeddings
 ↓
Nearest agent
```

No additional infrastructure will be introduced until Stage 1 becomes insufficient.

## Consequences

### Benefits

* avoids premature optimization
* preserves upgrade path

